@bvaradar 

Balaji - sincere apologies for not getting back earlier. The fact is that this happened only once and affected only 2 tables. I have reset the tables and since then, this issue has never resurfaced. I did see S3 logs etc to see if there was any abnormal activity at the platform infra level but there is nothing that we find. 

I shall wait to see and in the next deployment, I shall push the consistency guard option that you recommend. Thanks for all the help.

@xushiyan Thanks for the PR! 
Parquet support was recently added to the delta streamer in https://github.com/apache/incubator-hudi/pull/949. The plan will be to use the delta streamer for the initial parquet bulkinsert as well and retire HDFSParquetImporter. Would you like to use the delta streamer to do the HDFSParquetImporter work? I haven't used it in my production yet but would like to try it soon. If it doesn't work maybe we can make a PR to improve that. 
Thanks in advance!

@yanghua : I thought your test leverages DistributedTestDataSource and runs for long time and doing validations like counts check. Let me know if this is not the case ?

@n3nash test suite uses controlled orchestration and hive integration (white box like model) to create different scenarios and validate them.

IIUC, it sounds to me these are complementary and we will have uses for both.

